How to Add This Indicator to TradingView

Follow these steps to load this custom indicator onto your TradingView chart:

Step 1: Copy the Code from GitHub

Navigate to the .pine file (or text file) in this repository that contains the indicator code.
Click on the file to open it.
Click the "Copy raw contents" button (the two overlapping squares icon near the top right of the code box), or manually highlight and copy all the text.

Step 2: Open TradingView

Log into your TradingView account.
Open any active chart.

Step 3: Open the Pine Editor

Look at the very bottom of your TradingView chart screen.
Click on the Pine Editor tab. (If you don't see it, look for an arrow at the bottom of the screen to expand the bottom panel).

Step 4: Paste the Code

In the Pine Editor, you will likely see a few lines of default code (like //@version=5 and indicator("My script")).
Delete everything in that window so it is completely blank.
Paste the code you copied from GitHub into the empty Pine Editor window.

Step 5: Save and Apply

In the top right corner of the Pine Editor panel, click the Save button. Name the script whatever you like.
Once saved, click the Add to Chart button (located right next to the Save button).
The indicator should now appear on your chart!

Step 6: Adjust Settings (Optional)

Hover over the indicator's name in the top-left corner of your chart (or in a separate pane below the chart).
Click the Settings gear icon to adjust any inputs, colors, or styles to your preference.
